      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: Option C) Alkaloids</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Bitter taste:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Alkaloids are a class of naturally occurring organic compounds that often have bitter tastes.</li>\n\t<li>Various plants produce them as a defence mechanism against herbivores and insects.</li>\n\t<li>Many alkaloids are toxic or have pharmacological effects on the human body.</li>\n\t<li>Examples of alkaloids: are caffeine, nicotine, morphine, and quinine.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Aldehyde (Option A): </strong>Aldehydes and ketones have a sweet taste. Most sweet substances are organic. This option is incorrect.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Amino acids (Option B):</strong> α-amino acids have a sweet taste, but polypeptides are often bitter. This option is incorrect.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Hydrogen ions (Option D): </strong>Sour taste is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3978e9614f1692777200abbe4cfa34\">triggered</span> by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11f7bcb8da16927771898e93932195\">hydrogen</span> ions, the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc562fef3f16927771805b9a31499c\">adequate stimulus</span> being a pH of less than 4 of the solution. This option is incorrect.</p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following is not a characteristic of decerebrate rigidity according to the Herrington classification?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Rigidity occurs in all the muscles of the body"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Increase in the rate of discharge of the γ efferent neuron"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Increased excitability of the motor neuron pool"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Mid-collicular lesion can lead to decerebrate rigidity"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9ab07bba3016927771976de44bf865\">Rigidity</span> occurs in all the muscles of the body</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Decerebrate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9ab07bba3016927771976de44bf865\">rigidity</span> primarily affects the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45f9bc42ac16927771871c9dc2970a\">extensor</span> muscles of the limbs, leading to the characteristic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"115643fed616927771961316effc71\">posture</span> of rigid extension. It does not affect all the muscles of the body equally.</p>\n\n<p>According to the Herrington classification, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a243ecb6401692777186404bdb4792\">decerebrate rigidity</span> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1b06f401f1692777203a53393ba98\">form</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"458e050fdc16927771809854c9fd53\">abnormal</span> muscle tone that occurs due to damage or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3662597407169277718640a12868f5\">dysfunction</span> in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53abb386551692777192c4d1f1f5ed\">medulla</span> resulting in increased activity of motoneurons that facilitate stretch reflexes.</p>\n\n<p>Facilitation of stretch reflexes occurs due to two mechanisms:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Increased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3892cfe03616927771872f834cf855\">excitability</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"29e1987f81169277719209260ba0f1\">motor neuron</span> pool in general.</li>\n\t<li>Increased rate of γ <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"29e1987f81169277719209260ba0f1\">motor neuron</span> discharge.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Producing a mid-collicular <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d5e7bb15851692777191b39417c26a\">lesion</span> in an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9a33df37216927771877270a0f525\">experimental animal</span> results in decerebration.</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:733px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Decerebrate Rigidity</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Decorticate Rigidity</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>A state of severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"68f7148c4e1692777189074a8370ef\">hypertonia</span> characterized by extension of all four limbs.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>A state in which the upper extremities are flexed and the lower extremities are extended.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cause</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Damage to the lower <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d26464df7216927771923483619265\">midbrain</span> and upper pons</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Damage to the upper midbrain</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Mechanism</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Loss of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0cf8ac70611692777186b133d027f6\">descending</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f03ca2d2a716927771901227bc175a\">inhibition</span> to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a533b2d59f1692777196694dbb1b2a\">pontine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0b6b1f44cb1692777197afef785626\">reticular</span> system causes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d92c42574616927771946db516e33e\">overactivity</span> of this system, which excites <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e6f57b5b771692777181839b51f6ee\">antigravity</span> muscles.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Rubrospinal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a1307223f16927772017a994bfc39\">tract</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8265e091151692777187f264d73f3b\">excitation</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3674af39031692777202252504982a\">flexor</span> muscles in the upper extremities results in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"85ff8a7ff81692777202a827961a5c\">flexion</span> due to damage above the red nucleus.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Posture</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Arms adducted and extended</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Forearms pronated</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Wrists and fingers flexed</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Legs extended</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Feet <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a7a430f3a9169277719510c13f434d\">plantar</span> flexed</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Arms adducted and flexed</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Wrists and fingers flexed</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Legs extended</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Plantar <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"85ff8a7ff81692777202a827961a5c\">flexion</span> of the feet</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Clinical Significance</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2fd6b3cdf516927771836603ca8c63\">brain stem</span> damage; poor prognosis</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Better <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e580b4033e169277719609af594c16\">prognosis</span> than decerebrate rigidity</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2488\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/dX3cKlr1fVTHJ3IKyb4i1745932926.png\" width=\"3598\" /></p>",
