    {
      "text": "Which lobe is affected by a lesion that results in a deficit in hand-eye coordination?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Parietal lobe"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Frontal lobe"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Temporal lobe"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Occipital lobe"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p>Impairment of hand-eye <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3820ba101416927771858fe257e119\">coordination</span> is commonly associated with lesions in the brain’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> especially in the Brodmann area 5 and 7.</p>\n\n<p>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> integrates visual input from the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77dc7a0ab81692777194dba7ab78ab\">occipital</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> and motor output from the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"35aa36279d16927772031c7ce8d6e5\">frontal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> and acts as an association cortex.. It helps process and integrate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> inputs to guide motor movements and coordinate hand-eye interactions and is the most important area</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"Broadmanns-\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"12618\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"May2025\" height=\"666\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/9m6l7WHpUzp9rS9Fxgti1747059275.png\" width=\"600\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<h3><strong>Brodmann Areas: </strong></h3>\n\n<h3><strong>Definition</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Numbered regions of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ed2f4c790516927771840d0d99e9f4\">cerebral cortex</span> identified by Korbinian Brodmann, based on neuronal structure and arrangement.</li>\n\t<li>Linked to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> processing, motor control, and cognitive functions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Key Brodmann Areas and Functions</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:531px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Brodmann Area</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Function</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>1, 2, 3</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"be46da176016927771984a269a5b2c\">somatosensory</span> cortex; processes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ff110f2cb71692777200a3483aa670\">tactile</span> information.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>4</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Primary motor cortex; controls voluntary movements.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>5, 7</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Somatosensory association areas; integrate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> input.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>6</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Premotor/supplementary motor areas; plan movements.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>17</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Primary visual cortex; processes visual data.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>18, 19</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Visual association areas; advanced visual processing.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>22</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Wernicke's area; facilitates language comprehension.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>44, 45</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Broca's area; involved in speech production.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Frontal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> (Option B):</strong> The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"35aa36279d16927772031c7ce8d6e5\">frontal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> is responsible for motor output and is involved in the hand-eye movements, but the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> is the most important.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temporal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> (Option C)</strong>: The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"637ea4d17516927772003be2b2aae4\">temporal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> is mainly associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f17057f75016927771829e70074368\">auditory</span> processing, memory, and language functions, and lesions in this <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> typically do not cause significant impairments in hand-eye coordination.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Occipital <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> (Option D):</strong> The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77dc7a0ab81692777194dba7ab78ab\">occipital</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> is primarily responsible for visual processing and is involved in the hand-eye movements, but the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7dd6ae43c1692777191cf75c0bd58\">lobe</span> is the most important</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
